::Q01_Why_TypeScript: Why use TypeScript with Playwright?::
What is the main advantage of TypeScript in Playwright tests? {
=Detecting errors at compile time and better autocomplete
~Faster execution in the browser
~Ability to run tests without Node.js
~Built‑in support for mobile emulators
}

::Q02_Minimum_Config: Minimum tsconfig target for Playwright::
Which value of the `target` option is recommended in the example? {
=ES2020
~ES5
~ES2015
~ESNext
}

::Q03_Strict_mode: Strict typing mode::
What value of `strict` is recommended to avoid null/undefined issues? {
=true
~false
~"auto"
~"warn"
}

::Q04_ModuleResolution: ModuleResolution in a Playwright project::
Which `moduleResolution` value is used to correctly resolve `@playwright/test`? {
=node
~bundler
~classic
~nodenext
}

::Q05_Page_Locator: Page vs Locator types::
What best describes the difference between `Page` and `Locator`? {
=`Page` — a browser tab; `Locator` — a DOM element query
~`Page` — an HTTP response; `Locator` — a browser context
~`Page` — a CSS selector; `Locator` — a page URL
~`Page` — cookie storage; `Locator` — a network interceptor
}

::Q06_Use_Locator: When to use Locator instead of ElementHandle?::
Which approach is recommended by modern Playwright API? {
=Use `Locator`, since `ElementHandle` is discouraged for most scenarios
~Always use `ElementHandle`, because it is more stable
~Use `Locator` only for forms, everything else — `ElementHandle`
~It doesn't matter; both are equivalent
}

::Q07_Return_null: Can return null::
Which `Locator` method may return `string | null` and requires null handling? {
=textContent()
~innerText()
~inputValue()
~isVisible()
}

::Q08_Safer: Safer than any::
Which TypeScript type is considered safer than `any` because it requires narrowing? {
=unknown
~never
~void
~object
}

::Q09_Parameters: Optional parameters::
How do you mark an optional function parameter in TypeScript? {
=`param?: Type`
~`param!: Type`
~`param??: Type`
~`param|: Type`
}

::Q10_Union_Type: Browser union type::
Which value is NOT part of the union type `BrowserName = 'chromium' | 'firefox' | 'webkit'`? {
=safari
~chromium
~firefox
~webkit
}

::Q11_Interface_Alias: Interface vs type alias::
Which is better suited for describing object shapes and supports `extends`? {
=interface
~type alias
~enum
~class
}

::Q12_Utility_Partial: Utility type Partial::
What does `Partial<T>` do? {
=Makes all properties of T optional
~Removes specified keys from T
~Makes all properties required
~Converts an array into a tuple
}

::Q13_Utility_Pick: Utility type Pick::
Which statement is correct about `Pick<T, K>`? {
=Creates a type with a subset of properties K from T
~Creates a type without keys K from T
~Makes all properties optional
~Converts all values into `unknown`
}

::Q14_API: Typing API responses::
Which is a correct way to declare a generic API response interface? {
=`interface ApiResponse<T> { data: T; status: number; message: string; timestamp: Date; }`
~`type ApiResponse = { data: any; code: string }`
~`interface ApiResponse { payload: T[] }`
~`type ApiResponse<T> = T & number`
}

::Q15_Generics: Generics in functions::
What does `function getFirst<T>(arr: T[]): T` return? {
=The first element of an array of type T
~The length of the array as number
~The first two elements as an array
~Always a string
}

::Q16_Handling_Token: Handling token from Response::
What is the return type of a function that waits for `/api/login` and extracts `token`, which may be missing? {
=`Promise<string | null>`
~`Promise<string>`
~`string | null`
~`Promise<void>`
}

::Q17_Types: Importing Playwright types::
How do you import the `Page` and `Locator` types? {
=`import { Page, Locator } from '@playwright/test';`
~`import { Page, Locator } from 'playwright-core';`
~`import Page, { Locator } from '@playwright/test';`
~`import * as Page from '@playwright/test';`
}

::Q18_Configuring: Configuring paths::
Why configure `baseUrl` and `paths` in `tsconfig.json`? {
=To enable clean imports using aliases like `@pages/LoginPage`
~To enable headless mode in the browser
~To reduce test execution time
~To reduce screenshot size
}

::Q19_Fixtures: Typing Playwright fixtures::
Which construct allows extending `test` with typed fixtures? {
=`const test = base.extend<Pages>({ ... })`
~`const test = base.use<Pages>({ ... })`
~`const test = extend.base<Pages>({ ... })`
~`const test: Pages = base.extend({ ... })`
}

::Q20_Common_Async: Common async mistake::
Why is the function `function getPageTitle(page: Page) { return page.title(); }` problematic? {
=It returns a `Promise<string>` without explicit async/return type, which is misleading
~It blocks the Node.js event loop
~`title()` returns a number, not a string
~It cannot be used in tests
}
